<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,626,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,422,626,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">Nomenclatural notes:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="NY" collectorName="The &amp; Harris &amp; Britton &amp; According &amp; Berg &amp; Villavicencio &amp; Here" pageId="2" pageNumber="151" specimenCode="NY00532787" specimenCount="4" typeStatus="syntype">
<collectorName box="[422,466,626,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">The</collectorName>
protologue does not cite the herbarium in which the type, 
<emphasis box="[1125,1393,626,653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">
<collectorName box="[1125,1200,627,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">Harris</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[1237,1316,627,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">Britton</collectorName>
10765
</emphasis>
, was allocated. 
<collectorName box="[250,368,662,688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">According</collectorName>
to the code (Art. 7.11, note 2, ex. 13), when the herbarium was not mentioned, all specimens of that gathering are 
<typeStatus box="[335,433,699,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">syntypes</typeStatus>
and, therefore, a 
<typeStatus box="[623,726,698,724]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">lectotype</typeStatus>
must be designated. 
<collectorName box="[956,1010,699,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">Berg</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[1042,1191,698,724]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">Villavicencio</collectorName>
(2004) cited as type (in the work as “ 
<typeStatus box="[278,383,734,761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">holotype</typeStatus>
”) material deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[684,724,735,761]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="2" pageNumber="151" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
herbarium, however, this cannot be considered a lectotypification because it was published after 2001 and the “designated here” or a similar phrase was not used (Art. 7.11). 
<collectorName box="[1397,1451,771,797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">Here</collectorName>
we designate the material 
<specimenCode box="[437,589,806,833]" collectionCode="NY" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="2" pageNumber="151" type="Herbarium">NY00532787</specimenCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[674,777,806,832]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">lectotype</typeStatus>
because it contains well preserved syconia. Britton’s main herbarium is 
<collectionCode box="[284,321,843,869]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="2" pageNumber="151" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
, this also supports the choice
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,626,940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="151">
